methods.getTimeZone:
Returns the underlying Joda time zone for this DBTimeZone.

:return: (org.joda.time.DateTimeZone) the underlying Joda time zone.
methods.lookup:
Find the corresponding DBTimeZone for a given Joda DateTimeZone.

:param dateTimeZone: (org.joda.time.DateTimeZone) - the time zone to search for
:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.utils.DBTimeZone) the corresponding DBTimeZone, or null if none was found
methods.valueOf:
Returns the enum constant of this type with the specified name.
The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an
enum constant in this type.  (Extraneous whitespace characters are 
not permitted.)

:param name: (java.lang.String) - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.utils.DBTimeZone) the enum constant with the specified name
methods.valuesByOffset:
This method returns the same contents as values(), but ordered by geographic location / UTC
 offset. If two elements exist within the same timezone, they are second-order-sorted by name

:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.utils.DBTimeZone[]) An array of DBTimeZones ordered by UTC-offset

text: Defines Deephaven-supported timezones, which may be used for PQ-scheduling and display purposes
